An aerial view of Wang'uru township [Timothy Kariuki, Standard]  Kirinyaga County Assembly has passed a motion to upgrade Wang'uru town to a municipality.  Wang'uru will be the second municipality in Kirinyaga after Kerugoya/Kutus.   While moving the motion, Leader of Majority and Kerugoya MCA Kamau Murango noted that the move to elevate Wang’uru town into a municipality will unlock Sh600 million funding which will go towards financing a rice processing factory.    "By upgrading Wang'uru to a municipality, we shall attract key donors like the World Bank that are critical in financing infrastructure development in municipalities," said Murango.    Scolastica Nyawira, a nominated MCA, noted the move to upgrade Wang’uru to a municipality will generate more revenue and create employment opportunities.      By Boniface Gikandi | 4 hours ago By Phares Mutembei | 1 day ago By Jane Mugambi | 1 day ago By Muriithi Mugo | 1 day ago